You shouldn&#39;t create the `OnItemSelectedListener` inside the `OnClickListener` for your sign in button, instead you have to create it outside and save the selected option in a variable.

Then when the user clicks your sign in button, you check witch option was selected and start the correct **Activity**.

Looking at your code, you could simply save the intent to the next activity, and when the user clicks the button just start the **Activity** on that intent.

I&#39;ve put a check for nullity before trying to start that intent, and you could show the user some dialog or Toast if no valid option was selected.

    public class SignInActivity extends Activity {
    
